This paper involves the implementation of an algorithm for generating a knowledge network for commonsense reasoning, specifically with the application of robotic task repair. The paper uses Bayesian Logic Network (BLN) to represent the network and combines information from two existing knowledge sources: ConceptNet and WordNet. The paper also focuses on the situated structure learning of the network by including only relevant information in a given context. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
